Attention all community members! Let your voice be heard in the search for our next Superintendent!

All students, Faculty and Staff, and community members are welcome to participate in a Virtual Community Forum with Ray and Associates on Thursday, September 10th, at 10 AM or 6 PM via Zoom. These sessions will allow for a dialogue between our search consultants and groups of staff, students, and community while prioritizing safety during the current pandemic. Visit www.knusd331.com to register to attend one of the forums!

Link for Registration for the 10 AM Session: https://zoom.us/meeting/register/tJwuce-gpz8sG9Q4MnB-PU4yVnNIINxqRTfk

post_text: USD 331 is pleased to announce the reassignment of Mrs. Wendy Grimm from 3rd grade teacher at Norwich Elem to our preschool teacher. It’s actually a return to preschool for Mrs. Grimm who has passion for teaching all kids but really wanted to return to the “littles”. Welcome home! Mrs. Grimm hands 3rd grade over to Mrs. Hollie Carroll who will also be our Head Varsity Volleyball Coach at NHS.

post_text: USD 331 is very pleased to announce that Kingman Elementary teacher Mrs. Kelsy Higgins is going to change roles & will be an additional Counselor in the district. She will share responsibilities at both Kingman Middle & High 7-12 and at KES K-6. We are thrilled to be able to provide more professional help to kids to meet their social & emotional needs. In addition to being our newest Counselor, Kelsy is our new Head Varsity Volleyball Coach at KHS.

post_text: USD 331 is pleased to announce that Amy Wallace will be changing responsibilities for the coming year. She has been KMS Principal for 3 yrs. She will assume responsibilities previously held by Tammy Clark who is moving to Norwich 7-12 Principal to fill that position that opened up with the resignation of Dustin Little. Mrs. Wallace will be Principal of 331 Virtual Eagle & Adult Learning Services & District CTE Coordinator, secondary curriculum, among other duties. Mrs . Clark will be transitioning Virtual & Credit Recovery responsibilities to Mrs. Wallace over the summer. CTE will be over the next few months. Mr. Andy Albright & Mr. Rollie Van Wyhe will be adding responsibilities of 7th & 8th graders all day instead of afternoons only like we have done for the past four years. Mr. Bill Kelley will remain in his current role as Kingman preK-6 Principal and Mrs. Heidi Howard will continue as Norwich preK-6 Principal.

post_text: We know Kingman & Norwich Seniors & parents are anxious to hear what plans are for celebrating graduation. All plans are subject to Kansas moving to Phase 2 and to approval by the County Health Officer. The Governor announced today that there could be NO Graduation Events while Kansas is in Phase 1. We plan to have an alternative ceremony the weekend of May 22-24. Times & Details will be forthcoming. We also are planning a more traditional ceremony on Saturday, June 27.

USD 331 filed a waiver request to allow us to offer FREE meals (Breakfast & Lunch)to all kids ages 1 yr to 18 yrs old beginning Monday, March 23 in both Kingman & Norwich. We are very excited to announce this program for our schools & communities.
What will it look like?
•Similar to Summer Lunch Program
•Cost to All kids- $0.00 Free
•Will NOT eat at school
•Will probably be picked up in parking lot.
•possible distribution at other locations around town
•possible Home delivery (not sure)
•District will be sending communication by Weekend surveying all households Interest, How Many meals, preferred access to meals.

We know there are going to be a lot of questions related to the Governor’s school closing order. Very important: School Buildings were Closed. LEARNING has NOT Stopped. We are developing a Continuous Learning Plan for all students. Details will be forthcoming.
•No Students nor parents nor visitors will be allowed in school buildings this week.
•Only certain staff will be allowed in schools this week.
•Deep cleaning is being completed.
•Next week Teachers will return
•No Students nor non-employees will be allowed in school buildings until further notice.
•We plan to start serving Breakfast & Lunch to students NEXT week. Details will be shared by the end of this week.
•Questions will be answered as timely as possible but this site is not monitored continuously. You are urged to call district office, also.
620-532-3134

post_text: Official update on status of school at USD 331 today (Friday, January 17, 2020): We will continue with our plan to follow our Late Start schedule. The temperature is rising with lots of melting. There are isolated slick spots on streets, roads & highways so caution should be exercised. Sidewalks seem to be hazardous. School maintenance crews are at work spreading ice-melt on sidewalks. Parking lots are slick so be aware of that. Thanks to City, County, & State Road Crews for your advance treatment & for putting down sand to help keep us all safe. Parents- as always in weather decisions- if you are uncomfortable with our decision you can choose to keep your student(s) home. Remember we aren’t starting until 9:30 this morning. Also - remember we do not have school on Monday, Jan. 20 due to Inservice. Drive safely.

post_text:
USD 331 Schools in both Kingman & Norwich will use our LATE START schedule Tomorrow (Friday, January 17, 2020) due to the weather prediction of ice/freezing rain/snow overnight. Remember Late Start means School will start at 9:30 a.m. We hope the later start will give Mother Nature a chance to warm things up & start ice melting.
IF the weather & road conditions are worse than predicted then we will re-evaluate our decision & update parents, students and communities by 7:30 a.m on Friday if we need to cancel altogether.
As always in weather situations- parents use your best judgment and drive safely and remind your kids that are driving to take it easy, drive slower than normal and leave plenty of room to stop.

post_text:
Update on Lockdown event at Kingman Elementary & Middle School. At No Time were students or staff in danger.
At approximately 11:30 a.m. this morning, a 5th grade girl left KEMS without permission. We originally thought she was hiding in the school building so a lockdown of the school was initiated to facilitate a search for the student by staff and local police. As part of the search we reviewed video surveillance and determined she left the building. The search was then expanded to the blocks surrounding the school. The missing student was found ‪at 12:40‬ a couple of blocks from the school. She is safe and so are all students and staff in the school. At no point were any other students or staff in danger. Thank you to all staff and local police for a quick response leading to resolution to this event.

USD 331 is encouraging anyone interested in working to apply for an opening we have for a cook position at Kingman Elementary & Middle School starting 2nd semester. Please apply online at: www.knusd331.com

November 12th at 6:30 - 7:30 pm in the KHS auditorium
Join us for an informational meeting, open to parents, students, and patrons in the community, regarding teenage vaping. Kingman Schools are partnering with the Kingman Police Department to bring important information about this growing issue that is occurring, not only in our community, but across the nation. There will be vaping paraphernalia to view. We will also discuss the challenges we face in identifying and detecting vaping use and products. We hope to see you next Tuesday for this informative presentation.

USD 331 Kingman Elementary School
September 27, 2019 at 2:08 PM ·

We have two stories to share about the power of our Ohana groups. If you remember each week we have 48 groups in the building led by an adult and the groups have mixed ages of kids--a Kindergartener, 1st grader, all the way up to 8th grade. Today one of our family leaders put together an incentive for one of her boys if he can meet some goals they agreed on. During lunch, one of our little guys was having a hard time and without being asked, the 7th grader from his Ohana went right over to him and consoled him and calmed him down. This is the power of relationships that go across all age levels. ♥️

post_text: Congratulations to Travis and your entire Eck Services Team! Very “Eck-citing” to watch the phenomenal success of your company and to see so many employees that went through our schools. You are a part of our district and Kingman High success story! Awesome entrepreneurial spirit combined with hard work, grit and determination. #USD331EaglePride
shared_text:
Eck Services
August 21, 2019 at 9:00 AM ·

GREAT NEWS! Inc. Magazine has revealed that we are on its annual Inc. 5000 list, the most prestigious ranking of the nation’s fastest-growing private companies. Being on the Inc. 5000 list is an incredible honor especially since we are grouped with the likes of Microsoft, Pandora, Under Armour, and other trailblazing titans.

Thank you for trusting #EckServices with your plumbing, electrical and HVAC. We love what we do. 🌟

post_text: Thanks to City of Kingman and Convention & Tourism Committee for facilitating this promotional project. #USD331EaglePride
shared_text:
Kingman, Kansas-City of Kingman
August 12, 2019 at 3:26 PM ·

The promotion campaign spearheaded by the City's Convention & Tourism Committee with KWCH is ON THE AIR!!! There are 11, one-minute long commercials in this campaign to highlight not only the City, but also the 39 businesses that are a part of the campaign. The ads started running today and will continue over the next five months. This is a great way to draw attention to our great city! Thanks to everyone who participated in this new program!

We will post a different ad every few days, but look for the ads live on KWCH and KSCW. Part of this campaign also includes digital content on KWCH.com as well.
